tldr: The user requested to implement a database and an admin dashboard for a
  sleep questionnaire application based on a provided Statement of Work. The
  implementation included setting up a PostgreSQL database with Prisma, creating
  a simple password-protected admin dashboard with CSV export, and integrating
  Next.js middleware for authentication. The solution was successfully
  implemented and tested.
overview: The user aimed to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by adding
  database storage for responses and a client-facing admin dashboard. The
  approach involved using NeonDB with Prisma for PostgreSQL database management.
  A  model was created to store questionnaire data,
  including denormalized demographic information for easy retrieval. For the
  admin dashboard, a simple password-based authentication system was implemented
  using Next.js middleware to protect routes and manage sessions. The dashboard
  provides a table view of submitted responses and a CSV download option. The
  questionnaire form was updated to submit data to the new API endpoint. The
  implementation was successfully tested, confirming data submission, admin
  login, and CSV export functionality.
